text: Tawanta is an unincorporated community in Jones County, in the U.S. state of Mississippi. ==History== Tawanta was founded in 1882. The name "Tawanta" is purported to mean "wide, broad" in the Choctaw language. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Mississippi Category:Unincorporated communities in Jones County, Mississippi
title: Tawanta, Mississippi
